Nurse Ratchet, you do confuse me. I made myself a promise not to take anyone's opinion personally, but I must make an except for you. YOU PISS ME OFF. Your last post was absolutely incredible.  Allow me this last opportunity to tell you what a twit you are. Please go back to your classroom in the halls of academia, god knows the streets of reality might just dirty your prissy &quot;thoughts&quot;.<br><br>
Not that I think much of your need to take personal hits on me, but for your admission, and gall, that you did nothing during the war, NOTHING, you admit you were never involved, &quot;knew&quot; you weren't going to Nam, just hid behind the deferrment system while others died or did their time, but enough of that, I mean OH LORD, you taught at a tough school, and therefore think you know something. Give us a break. <br><br>
Good God. The Nurse is really social science teacher.  Move over Nurse Ratchet, looks more like Welcome Home Kotter, or what ever that insipid show was called. More like Al Bundy has joined the chat. <br><br>
People in here, dear teacher, are spilling their guts and their intermost thoughts to heal, to touch, to communicate, NOT to entertain you. NOT TO GIVE YOU A CHEAP THRILL !  This isn't some High School term paper, but then again, I don't think you would know the difference if it jumped up and bit you on your liberal academic ass. <br><br>
Now that we know you are not some cross dresser, but a 50 year old social science teacher who wasn't drafted or ever even had the strength of convictions to protest, (hence I assume you are &quot;male&quot;), you do lose all your credibility when you state that you &quot;knew&quot; that if drafted you weren't going to Viet Nam. I think you have been in the classroom too long, and not out here, on the streets of life and reality. Thank God I'm not in your class as I suspect you are one of those institutionalize &quot;teachers&quot; who can't handle students who challenge your stale thoughts and worse opinions.  <br><br>
Why don't you download this and post it in your classroom for a week?  Could you handle the feedback from your students?<br><br>
I gave you a compliment and you return it with a snide &quot;up to his old tricks again&quot; remark.  Get a life, Nurse Teacher, one that is gender correct, and stop offering opinion based on your fantasies and unthinking inaccuracies. You are the very thing you wish to warn other's children about. We will always have us versus them, Black vs. Whites, Bloods v. Crips as long as intellectual academic's such as you think they can stand above the fray and offer their viewpoint as if it is special and rare.  Rare my ass.<br><br>
You &quot;protested with my vote&quot;. Oh for Christ's Sakes, who is trolling for a fight now? Even my 14 year old daughter thinks you are a wienie.  What Bull Shit. &quot;Protest with my vote&quot;, OH what a cop out.  Got to be the worst thing I have yet to read on these posts.<br><br>
Enough.  I apologize to the rest of the readers of this post for &quot;losing it&quot; as I have. I considered deleting all of this, but choose not to.  I ask all the readers to see Nurse Ratchet for the evil that he really represents.   This is the true American who cheered the body count on the evening news, smug in his beliefs that he was safe, hiding behind the deferrment system and his &quot;beliefs&quot; that he wasn't going to Nam. Of course, given his beliefs, Viet Nam will repeat over and over and over.   <br><br>
Thank God, I am about as opposite from you as one can be.  How many years have you been teaching from the same lesson plan to a world that changes every month?  Only your students will know, or suffer, your inflated and outdated narcissistic ego.<br><br>
To my friends and fellow survivors I am Barry, but to you, teach, Doctor Spatz will suffice.<br><br>
flamingly yours....<br><br>

